{"cursor":"5468","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":" \n\nIn the post-production process of film editing and video editing, a 'cut' is an\nabrupt, but usually trivial film transition from one sequence to another. It is\nsynonymous with the term edit, though \"edit\" can imply any number of transitions\nor effects. The cut, dissolve and wipe serve as the three primary transitions.\nThe term refers to the physical action of cutting film or videotape, but also\nrefers to a similar edit performed in software; it has also become associated\nwith the resulting visual \"break\".\n","linknr":136,"url":"Cut_(transition)","recorded":1362674371,"links":16,"instances":["wine","speed","transition","fiction","actor","film","film","film"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Film techniques","Film editing"],"headings":["History","\"Cut!\"","The proper cut","Variations","See also"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["dissolve","film"],["wipe","transition"],["director","film"],["shot","film"],["extra","actor"],["setting","fiction"],["pace","speed"],["dissolve","film"],["wipe","transition"],["champagne","wine"]],"members":["champagne","pace","wipe","setting","extra","dissolve","shot","director"],"related":["Post-production","Film_editing","Video_editing","Film_transition","Dissolve_(film)","Wipe_(transition)","Film_stock","Film_splicer","Actuality_films","Director_(film)","Shot_(film)","Narrative","Clapperboard","Extra_(actor)","Suspension_of_disbelief","Setting_(fiction)","Time","Pace_(speed)","Continuity_editing","Establishing_shot","Medium_shot","Tracking_shot","Dialogue","Close-up","180-degree_rule","Multiple-camera_setup","Vision_mixer","Linear_video_editing","Non-linear_edi